text: Frances Janse van Rensburg (born 10 January 2001) is a South African road racing cyclist. She competed at the 2021 UCI Road World Championships, in the women's time trial event and women's road race event. She won multiple medals at the African Cycling Championships. She races with Stade Rochelais Charente- Maritime. == References == Category:2001 births Category:Cyclists Category:South African sportspeople Category:Living people
